        <!-- Section 1: Concept and Nature -->
        <section id="concept" class="mb-20">
          <div class="flex items-center gap-4 mb-8">
            <div
              class="w-12 h-12 bg-primary rounded-full flex items-center justify-center"
            >
              <span class="text-white font-bold">1</span>
            </div>
            <h2 class="font-serif text-4xl font-bold text-gray-900">
              Concept and Nature of Organizational Behavior
            </h2>
          </div>

          <div class="grid grid-cols-1 lg:grid-cols-3 gap-8 mb-12">
            <div class="lg:col-span-2">
              <h3 class="font-serif text-2xl font-bold text-primary mb-6">
                Definition and Core Meaning
              </h3>
              <div class="prose-custom text-gray-700 mb-6">
                <p class="mb-4">
                  Organizational Behavior (OB) represents a systematic field of
                  inquiry dedicated to understanding, predicting, and managing
                  human behavior within organizational settings. At its
                  foundational level, OB integrates knowledge from multiple
                  behavioral sciences to examine what people think, feel, and do
                  in and around organizations, with the explicit purpose of
                  enhancing both organizational effectiveness and individual
                  well-being
                  <a
                    href="https://theintactone.com/2024/12/04/disciplines-contributing-to-organisational-behaviour-ob/"
                    class="citation-link"
                    >[614]</a
                  >.
                </p>
                <p class="mb-4">
                  The classical definitions of OB emphasize three interconnected
                  functions that guide research and practice.
                  <strong>Fred Luthans</strong>, in his seminal work
                  <em>Organizational Behavior: An Evidence-Based Approach</em>,
                  defines OB as &#34;the understanding, prediction, and
                  management of human behavior in organizations&#34;
                  <a
                    href="https://dscet.ac.in/questionbank/mba/first-sem/OB.pdf"
                    class="citation-link"
                    >[397]</a
                  >.
                </p>
              </div>
            </div>
            <div class="bg-secondary rounded-xl p-6">
              <h4 class="font-serif text-lg font-bold text-primary mb-4">
                TU-Specific Definition
              </h4>
              <div class="space-y-4 text-sm text-gray-700">
                <div class="flex items-start gap-3">
                  <div class="w-2 h-2 bg-primary rounded-full mt-2"></div>
                  <div>
                    <strong>Understanding:</strong> Descriptive function of
                    documenting behavioral patterns
                  </div>
                </div>
                <div class="flex items-start gap-3">
                  <div class="w-2 h-2 bg-primary rounded-full mt-2"></div>
                  <div>
                    <strong>Prediction:</strong> Anticipating employee responses
                    to managerial actions
                  </div>
                </div>
                <div class="flex items-start gap-3">
                  <div class="w-2 h-2 bg-primary rounded-full mt-2"></div>
                  <div>
                    <strong>Control:</strong> Responsible design of
                    organizational conditions
                  </div>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>

          <!-- Scope and Domain -->
          <div class="mb-12">
            <h3 class="font-serif text-2xl font-bold text-primary mb-6">
              Scope and Domain of OB
            </h3>
            <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-3 gap-6">
              <div
                class="bg-white border border-gray-200 rounded-xl p-6 hover:shadow-lg transition-shadow"
              >
                <div
                  class="w-12 h-12 bg-primary/10 rounded-lg flex items-center justify-center mb-4"
                >
                  <i class="fas fa-user text-primary text-xl"></i>
                </div>
                <h4 class="font-serif text-lg font-bold text-gray-900 mb-3">
                  Individual Level
                </h4>
                <p class="text-gray-700 text-sm mb-3">
                  Personality, perception, motivation, learning
                </p>
                <ul class="text-sm text-gray-600 space-y-1">
                  <li>• Big Five personality theory</li>
                  <li>• Perceptual processes</li>
                  <li>• Motivation theories</li>
                </ul>
              </div>
              <div
                class="bg-white border border-gray-200 rounded-xl p-6 hover:shadow-lg transition-shadow"
              >
                <div
                  class="w-12 h-12 bg-primary/10 rounded-lg flex items-center justify-center mb-4"
                >
                  <i class="fas fa-users text-primary text-xl"></i>
                </div>
                <h4 class="font-serif text-lg font-bold text-gray-900 mb-3">
                  Group Level
                </h4>
                <p class="text-gray-700 text-sm mb-3">
                  Team dynamics, leadership, communication
                </p>
                <ul class="text-sm text-gray-600 space-y-1">
                  <li>• Group development stages</li>
                  <li>• Leadership theories</li>
                  <li>• Conflict management</li>
                </ul>
              </div>
              <div
                class="bg-white border border-gray-200 rounded-xl p-6 hover:shadow-lg transition-shadow"
              >
                <div
                  class="w-12 h-12 bg-primary/10 rounded-lg flex items-center justify-center mb-4"
                >
                  <i class="fas fa-building text-primary text-xl"></i>
                </div>
                <h4 class="font-serif text-lg font-bold text-gray-900 mb-3">
                  System Level
                </h4>
                <p class="text-gray-700 text-sm mb-3">
                  Structure, culture, change, development
                </p>
                <ul class="text-sm text-gray-600 space-y-1">
                  <li>• Organizational structure</li>
                  <li>• Culture management</li>
                  <li>• Change processes</li>
                </ul>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>

          <!-- Goals and Objectives -->
          <div class="bg-gray-50 rounded-xl p-8">
            <h3 class="font-serif text-2xl font-bold text-primary mb-6">
              Goals and Objectives of Studying OB
            </h3>
            <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-3 gap-6">
              <div class="text-center">
                <div
                  class="w-16 h-16 bg-primary/10 rounded-full flex items-center justify-center mx-auto mb-4"
                >
                  <i class="fas fa-search text-primary text-2xl"></i>
                </div>
                <h4 class="font-serif text-lg font-bold text-gray-900 mb-2">
                  Descriptive
                </h4>
                <p class="text-gray-700 text-sm">
                  Understanding behavioral patterns through systematic
                  observation and analysis
                </p>
              </div>
              <div class="text-center">
                <div
                  class="w-16 h-16 bg-primary/10 rounded-full flex items-center justify-center mx-auto mb-4"
                >
                  <i class="fas fa-crystal-ball text-primary text-2xl"></i>
                </div>
                <h4 class="font-serif text-lg font-bold text-gray-900 mb-2">
                  Predictive
                </h4>
                <p class="text-gray-700 text-sm">
                  Anticipating employee responses to policies, changes, and
                  managerial actions
                </p>
              </div>
              <div class="text-center">
                <div
                  class="w-16 h-16 bg-primary/10 rounded-full flex items-center justify-center mx-auto mb-4"
                >
                  <i class="fas fa-cogs text-primary text-2xl"></i>
                </div>
                <h4 class="font-serif text-lg font-bold text-gray-900 mb-2">
                  Control
                </h4>
                <p class="text-gray-700 text-sm">
                  Managing behavior through responsible design of organizational
                  conditions
                </p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </section>

        <!-- Section 2: Foundations -->
        <section id="foundations" class="mb-20">
          <div class="flex items-center gap-4 mb-8">
            <div
              class="w-12 h-12 bg-primary rounded-full flex items-center justify-center"
            >
              <span class="text-white font-bold">2</span>
            </div>
            <h2 class="font-serif text-4xl font-bold text-gray-900">
              Foundations of Organizational Behavior
            </h2>
          </div>

          <!-- Historical Evolution -->
          <div class="mb-12">
            <h3 class="font-serif text-2xl font-bold text-primary mb-6">
              Historical Evolution of OB
            </h3>

            <!-- Scientific Management Era -->
            <div class="mb-8">
              <h4 class="font-serif text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4">
                Scientific Management Era (1880s-1920s)
              </h4>
              <div class="bg-white border-l-4 border-primary p-6 mb-6">
                <div class="flex items-start gap-4">
                  <img
                    src="https://kimi-web-img.moonshot.cn/img/npg.si.edu/931b48b94f84dc394f53474cd22d80b707a394d8.jpg"
                    alt="Frederick Winslow Taylor portrait"
                    class="w-24 h-24 rounded-lg object-cover"
                    size="small"
                    aspect="square"
                    style="photo"
                    query="Frederick Winslow Taylor portrait"
                    referrerpolicy="no-referrer"
                    data-modified="1"
                    data-score="0.00"
                  />
                  <div class="flex-1">
                    <h5 class="font-bold text-gray-900 mb-2">
                      Frederick Winslow Taylor
                    </h5>
                    <p class="text-gray-700 mb-3">
                      Developed principles for optimizing manual work through
                      scientific selection and training of workers, scientific
                      determination of work methods, and division of work
                      between management (planning) and workers (execution)
                      <a
                        href="https://cvru.ac.in/PDFDoc/IODE/study-materials/MBA/Sem-1/1MBA1-Management-Process-and-Organizational-Behavior.pdf"
                        class="citation-link"
                        >[490]</a
                      >.
                    </p>
                    <div class="bg-gray-50 p-3 rounded text-sm">
                      <strong>Key Contribution:</strong> Demonstrated that
                      productivity could be dramatically increased through
                      systematic analysis—sometimes by factors of 200-400%.
                    </div>
                  </div>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>

            <!-- Human Relations Movement -->
            <div class="mb-8">
              <h4 class="font-serif text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4">
                Human Relations Movement (1920s-1950s)
              </h4>
              <div class="bg-secondary rounded-xl p-6">
                <h5 class="font-serif text-lg font-bold text-primary mb-3">
                  The Hawthorne Studies
                </h5>
                <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">
                  Landmark research conducted at Western Electric Company&#39;s
                  Hawthorne Works (1924-1932) revealed that social and
                  psychological factors were more influential than physical
                  working conditions in determining productivity
                  <a
                    href="https://cvru.ac.in/PDFDoc/IODE/study-materials/MBA/Sem-1/1MBA1-Management-Process-and-Organizational-Behavior.pdf"
                    class="citation-link"
                    >[200]</a
                  >.
                </p>
                <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
                  <div class="bg-white p-4 rounded-lg">
                    <h6 class="font-bold text-gray-900 mb-2">Key Findings</h6>
                    <ul class="text-sm text-gray-700 space-y-1">
                      <li>
                        • &#34;Hawthorne effect&#34;—improved performance from
                        attention
                      </li>
                      <li>• Social situation affects productivity</li>
                      <li>• Informal group dynamics influence output</li>
                    </ul>
                  </div>
                  <div class="bg-white p-4 rounded-lg">
                    <h6 class="font-bold text-gray-900 mb-2">Legacy</h6>
                    <ul class="text-sm text-gray-700 space-y-1">
                      <li>• Legitimized social science methods</li>
                      <li>• Demonstrated power of social factors</li>
                      <li>• Founded OB as distinct field</li>
                    </ul>
                  </div>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>

            <!-- Behavioral Science Approach -->
            <div class="mb-8">
              <h4 class="font-serif text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4">
                Behavioral Science Approach (1950s-1980s)
              </h4>
              <div class="overflow-x-auto">
                <table
                  class="w-full border-collapse border border-gray-300 text-sm"
                >
                  <thead class="bg-gray-50">
                    <tr>
                      <th
                        class="border border-gray-300 p-3 text-left font-bold"
                      >
                        Theory
                      </th>
                      <th
                        class="border border-gray-300 p-3 text-left font-bold"
                      >
                        Developer(s)
                      </th>
                      <th
                        class="border border-gray-300 p-3 text-left font-bold"
                      >
                        Core Contribution
                      </th>
                      <th
                        class="border border-gray-300 p-3 text-left font-bold"
                      >
                        OB Application
                      </th>
                    </tr>
                  </thead>
                  <tbody class="bg-white">
                    <tr>
                      <td class="border border-gray-300 p-3 font-semibold">
                        Hierarchy of Needs
                      </td>
                      <td class="border border-gray-300 p-3">Abraham Maslow</td>
                      <td class="border border-gray-300 p-3">
                        Human needs arranged in prepotent hierarchy:
                        physiological, safety, social, esteem,
                        self-actualization
                      </td>
                      <td class="border border-gray-300 p-3">
                        Understanding motivation; designing reward systems
                      </td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                      <td class="border border-gray-300 p-3 font-semibold">
                        Theory X and Theory Y
                      </td>
                      <td class="border border-gray-300 p-3">
                        Douglas McGregor
                      </td>
                      <td class="border border-gray-300 p-3">
                        Two contrasting assumptions about human nature: X
                        (control needed) vs. Y (self-direction possible)
                      </td>
                      <td class="border border-gray-300 p-3">
                        Managerial philosophy shapes employee treatment
                      </td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                      <td class="border border-gray-300 p-3 font-semibold">
                        Two-Factor Theory
                      </td>
                      <td class="border border-gray-300 p-3">
                        Frederick Herzberg
                      </td>
                      <td class="border border-gray-300 p-3">
                        Separate factors cause satisfaction (motivators) and
                        dissatisfaction (hygiene factors)
                      </td>
                      <td class="border border-gray-300 p-3">
                        Job enrichment focusing on motivators
                      </td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                      <td class="border border-gray-300 p-3 font-semibold">
                        Expectancy Theory
                      </td>
                      <td class="border border-gray-300 p-3">Victor Vroom</td>
                      <td class="border border-gray-300 p-3">
                        Motivation = Expectancy × Instrumentality × Valence
                      </td>
                      <td class="border border-gray-300 p-3">
                        Diagnostic tool for motivation problems
                      </td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                      <td class="border border-gray-300 p-3 font-semibold">
                        Contingency Theory
                      </td>
                      <td class="border border-gray-300 p-3">Fred Fiedler</td>
                      <td class="border border-gray-300 p-3">
                        Leadership effectiveness depends on match between leader
                        style and situational favorableness
                      </td>
                      <td class="border border-gray-300 p-3">
                        Leader selection or situation modification
                      </td>
                    </tr>
                  </tbody>
                </table>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>

          <!-- Contributing Disciplines -->
          <div class="mb-12">
            <h3 class="font-serif text-2xl font-bold text-primary mb-6">
              Contributing Disciplines to OB
            </h3>
            <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-3 gap-6">
              <div class="bg-white border border-gray-200 rounded-xl p-6">
                <div
                  class="w-12 h-12 bg-blue-100 rounded-lg flex items-center justify-center mb-4"
                >
                  <i class="fas fa-brain text-blue-600 text-xl"></i>
                </div>
                <h4 class="font-serif text-lg font-bold text-gray-900 mb-3">
                  Psychology
                </h4>
                <p class="text-gray-700 text-sm mb-3">
                  Scientific study of individual behavior and mental processes.
                </p>
                <ul class="text-xs text-gray-600 space-y-1">
                  <li>• Learning theory</li>
                  <li>• Personality assessment</li>
                  <li>• Motivation research</li>
                  <li>• Performance appraisal</li>
                </ul>
              </div>
              <div class="bg-white border border-gray-200 rounded-xl p-6">
                <div
                  class="w-12 h-12 bg-green-100 rounded-lg flex items-center justify-center mb-4"
                >
                  <i class="fas fa-user-friends text-green-600 text-xl"></i>
                </div>
                <h4 class="font-serif text-lg font-bold text-gray-900 mb-3">
                  Social Psychology
                </h4>
                <p class="text-gray-700 text-sm mb-3">
                  Individual behavior in social contexts.
                </p>
                <ul class="text-xs text-gray-600 space-y-1">
                  <li>• Attitude change</li>
                  <li>• Group processes</li>
                  <li>• Communication</li>
                  <li>• Decision-making</li>
                </ul>
              </div>
              <div class="bg-white border border-gray-200 rounded-xl p-6">
                <div
                  class="w-12 h-12 bg-purple-100 rounded-lg flex items-center justify-center mb-4"
                >
                  <i class="fas fa-users text-purple-600 text-xl"></i>
                </div>
                <h4 class="font-serif text-lg font-bold text-gray-900 mb-3">
                  Sociology
                </h4>
                <p class="text-gray-700 text-sm mb-3">
                  Social structures and collective behavior.
                </p>
                <ul class="text-xs text-gray-600 space-y-1">
                  <li>• Group dynamics</li>
                  <li>• Organizational culture</li>
                  <li>• Power and conflict</li>
                  <li>• Social change</li>
                </ul>
              </div>
              <div class="bg-white border border-gray-200 rounded-xl p-6">
                <div
                  class="w-12 h-12 bg-orange-100 rounded-lg flex items-center justify-center mb-4"
                >
                  <i class="fas fa-globe text-orange-600 text-xl"></i>
                </div>
                <h4 class="font-serif text-lg font-bold text-gray-900 mb-3">
                  Anthropology
                </h4>
                <p class="text-gray-700 text-sm mb-3">
                  Cross-cultural analysis and meaning systems.
                </p>
                <ul class="text-xs text-gray-600 space-y-1">
                  <li>• Cultural dimensions</li>
                  <li>• Comparative values</li>
                  <li>• Organizational ethnography</li>
                  <li>• Cross-cultural management</li>
                </ul>
              </div>
              <div class="bg-white border border-gray-200 rounded-xl p-6">
                <div
                  class="w-12 h-12 bg-red-100 rounded-lg flex items-center justify-center mb-4"
                >
                  <i class="fas fa-balance-scale text-red-600 text-xl"></i>
                </div>
                <h4 class="font-serif text-lg font-bold text-gray-900 mb-3">
                  Political Science
                </h4>
                <p class="text-gray-700 text-sm mb-3">
                  Power, governance, and conflict resolution.
                </p>
                <ul class="text-xs text-gray-600 space-y-1">
                  <li>• Organizational politics</li>
                  <li>• Authority relationships</li>
                  <li>• Negotiation strategies</li>
                  <li>• Empowerment</li>
                </ul>
              </div>
              <div class="bg-white border border-gray-200 rounded-xl p-6">
                <div
                  class="w-12 h-12 bg-yellow-100 rounded-lg flex items-center justify-center mb-4"
                >
                  <i class="fas fa-chart-line text-yellow-600 text-xl"></i>
                </div>
                <h4 class="font-serif text-lg font-bold text-gray-900 mb-3">
                  Economics
                </h4>
                <p class="text-gray-700 text-sm mb-3">
                  Rational choice and incentive structures.
                </p>
                <ul class="text-xs text-gray-600 space-y-1">
                  <li>• Human capital theory</li>
                  <li>• Agency theory</li>
                  <li>• Transaction cost analysis</li>
                  <li>• Behavioral economics</li>
                </ul>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>

          <!-- Basic Assumptions -->
          <div class="bg-gray-50 rounded-xl p-8">
            <h3 class="font-serif text-2xl font-bold text-primary mb-6">
              Basic Assumptions About Human Nature
            </h3>
            <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-8">
              <div class="space-y-6">
                <div class="flex items-start gap-4">
                  <div
                    class="w-8 h-8 bg-primary/10 rounded-full flex items-center justify-center flex-shrink-0 mt-1"
                  >
                    <i class="fas fa-user text-primary text-sm"></i>
                  </div>
                  <div>
                    <h4 class="font-bold text-gray-900 mb-2">
                      Individual Differences
                    </h4>
                    <p class="text-gray-700 text-sm">
                      People vary substantially in abilities, personalities,
                      values, needs, and motivations. Effective management
                      requires matching people to jobs and tailoring
                      motivational strategies
                      <a
                        href="https://mrcet.com/downloads/MBA/Management%20and%20Organisational%20Behaviour.pdf"
                        class="citation-link"
                        >[481]</a
                      >.
                    </p>
                  </div>
                </div>
                <div class="flex items-start gap-4">
                  <div
                    class="w-8 h-8 bg-primary/10 rounded-full flex items-center justify-center flex-shrink-0 mt-1"
                  >
                    <i class="fas fa-arrow-right text-primary text-sm"></i>
                  </div>
                  <div>
                    <h4 class="font-bold text-gray-900 mb-2">
                      Behavior as Caused and Directed
                    </h4>
                    <p class="text-gray-700 text-sm">
                      Human actions are not random but result from identifiable
                      factors—internal (needs, cognitions) or external (rewards,
                      social pressure)—that can be understood and influenced
                      <a
                        href="https://abit.edu.in/wp-content/uploads/2022/07/1st-sem-OB.pdf"
                        class="citation-link"
                        >[429]</a
                      >.
                    </p>
                  </div>
                </div>
              </div>
              <div class="space-y-6">
                <div class="flex items-start gap-4">
                  <div
                    class="w-8 h-8 bg-primary/10 rounded-full flex items-center justify-center flex-shrink-0 mt-1"
                  >
                    <i class="fas fa-eye text-primary text-sm"></i>
                  </div>
                  <div>
                    <h4 class="font-bold text-gray-900 mb-2">
                      Perception and Reality
                    </h4>
                    <p class="text-gray-700 text-sm">
                      People respond to their perceptions of reality rather than
                      to objective reality itself. Perception is an active,
                      constructive process influenced by individual
                      characteristics and social context
                      <a
                        href="https://www.dimr.edu.in/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/GC-102-OrganisationalBehvaiour_Notes_DivA_DivC_UpdatedVersion_Dr.RachanaDIMR.pdf"
                        class="citation-link"
                        >[524]</a
                      >.
                    </p>
                  </div>
                </div>
                <div class="flex items-start gap-4">
                  <div
                    class="w-8 h-8 bg-primary/10 rounded-full flex items-center justify-center flex-shrink-0 mt-1"
                  >
                    <i class="fas fa-heart text-primary text-sm"></i>
                  </div>
                  <div>
                    <h4 class="font-bold text-gray-900 mb-2">
                      Human Dignity and Ethical Treatment
                    </h4>
                    <p class="text-gray-700 text-sm">
                      People deserve respect and fair treatment regardless of
                      their organizational role or performance. Management
                      practices should enhance rather than diminish human
                      welfare
                      <a
                        href="https://mrcet.com/downloads/MBA/Management%20and%20Organisational%20Behaviour.pdf"
                        class="citation-link"
                        >[481]</a
                      >.
                    </p>
                  </div>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </section>

        <!-- Section 3: Contextual Perspectives -->
        <section id="contextual" class="mb-20">
          <div class="flex items-center gap-4 mb-8">
            <div
              class="w-12 h-12 bg-primary rounded-full flex items-center justify-center"
            >
              <span class="text-white font-bold">3</span>
            </div>
            <h2 class="font-serif text-4xl font-bold text-gray-900">
              Contextual Perspectives of Organizational Behavior
            </h2>
          </div>

          <div class="mb-8">
            <p class="text-lg text-gray-700 mb-6">
              The contextual perspectives of OB represent alternative
              philosophical and practical orientations toward managing people in
              organizations. These five approaches—Human Resources,
              Productivity, Interactionalism, Contingency, and Systems—are
              explicitly specified in the TU MBS syllabus
              <a
                href="https://www.fomecd.edu.np/syllabuses/MBS%201st%20Sem%20Syllabus%202018.pdf"
                class="citation-link"
                >[469]</a
              >
              <a
                href="https://digitallyeducate.com/contextual-perspective-of-organizational-behavior/"
                class="citation-link"
                >[473]</a
              >.
            </p>
          </div>

          <!-- Human Resources Approach -->
          <div class="mb-12">
            <h3 class="font-serif text-2xl font-bold text-primary mb-6">
              Human Resources Approach
            </h3>
            <div class="grid grid-cols-1 lg:grid-cols-2 gap-8 mb-8">
              <div>
                <h4 class="font-serif text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4">
                  Core Philosophy: People as Valuable Assets
                </h4>
                <div class="bg-secondary rounded-lg p-6 mb-6">
                  <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">
                    The HR approach represents a fundamental philosophical shift
                    from viewing employees as costs to be minimized to
                    recognizing them as valuable assets worthy of investment
                    <a
                      href="https://digitallyeducate.com/contextual-perspective-of-organizational-behavior/"
                      class="citation-link"
                      >[101]</a
                    >.
                  </p>
                  <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-3 gap-4">
                    <div class="text-center">
                      <div
                        class="w-12 h-12 bg-primary/10 rounded-full flex items-center justify-center mx-auto mb-2"
                      >
                        <i class="fas fa-seedling text-primary"></i>
                      </div>
                      <p class="text-xs font-semibold">Untapped Potential</p>
                    </div>
                    <div class="text-center">
                      <div
                        class="w-12 h-12 bg-primary/10 rounded-full flex items-center justify-center mx-auto mb-2"
                      >
                        <i class="fas fa-handshake text-primary"></i>
                      </div>
                      <p class="text-xs font-semibold">
                        Meaningful Contribution
                      </p>
                    </div>
                    <div class="text-center">
                      <div
                        class="w-12 h-12 bg-primary/10 rounded-full flex items-center justify-center mx-auto mb-2"
                      >
                        <i class="fas fa-chart-line text-primary"></i>
                      </div>
                      <p class="text-xs font-semibold">Investment Returns</p>
                    </div>
                  </div>
                </div>
              </div>
              <div>
                <h4 class="font-serif text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4">
                  Focus Areas
                </h4>
                <div class="space-y-4">
                  <div class="bg-white border border-gray-200 rounded-lg p-4">
                    <h5 class="font-bold text-gray-900 mb-2">
                      Employee Development
                    </h5>
                    <p class="text-sm text-gray-700">
                      Training, education, challenging assignments, career
                      planning
                    </p>
                  </div>
                  <div class="bg-white border border-gray-200 rounded-lg p-4">
                    <h5 class="font-bold text-gray-900 mb-2">Empowerment</h5>
                    <p class="text-sm text-gray-700">
                      Delegation of authority, access to information, autonomous
                      decision-making
                    </p>
                  </div>
                  <div class="bg-white border border-gray-200 rounded-lg p-4">
                    <h5 class="font-bold text-gray-900 mb-2">Participation</h5>
                    <p class="text-sm text-gray-700">
                      Quality circles, suggestion systems, representative
                      participation
                    </p>
                  </div>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>

            <!-- Managerial Role Transformation -->
            <div class="bg-white border border-gray-200 rounded-xl p-6">
              <h4 class="font-serif text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4">
                Managerial Role: From Controller to Facilitator
              </h4>
              <div class="overflow-x-auto">
                <table class="w-full border-collapse">
                  <thead class="bg-gray-50">
                    <tr>
                      <th
                        class="border border-gray-300 p-3 text-left font-bold"
                      >
                        Traditional Role
                      </th>
                      <th
                        class="border border-gray-300 p-3 text-left font-bold"
                      >
                        HR Approach Role
                      </th>
                      <th
                        class="border border-gray-300 p-3 text-left font-bold"
                      >
                        Required Skills
                      </th>
                    </tr>
                  </thead>
                  <tbody>
                    <tr>
                      <td class="border border-gray-300 p-3 text-sm">
                        Controller and director
                      </td>
                      <td class="border border-gray-300 p-3 text-sm">
                        Facilitator—creating conditions for success
                      </td>
                      <td class="border border-gray-300 p-3 text-sm">
                        Listening, questioning, removing obstacles
                      </td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                      <td class="border border-gray-300 p-3 text-sm">
                        Monitor and evaluator
                      </td>
                      <td class="border border-gray-300 p-3 text-sm">
                        Coach—developing subordinate capabilities
                      </td>
                      <td class="border border-gray-300 p-3 text-sm">
                        Giving feedback, developmental assignments
                      </td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                      <td class="border border-gray-300 p-3 text-sm">
                        Decision-maker
                      </td>
                      <td class="border border-gray-300 p-3 text-sm">
                        Resource provider—ensuring people have what they need
                      </td>
                      <td class="border border-gray-300 p-3 text-sm">
                        Securing resources, advocating for team
                      </td>
                    </tr>
                  </tbody>
                </table>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>

          <!-- Productivity Approach -->
          <div class="mb-12">
            <h3 class="font-serif text-2xl font-bold text-primary mb-6">
              Productivity Approach
            </h3>
            <div class="grid grid-cols-1 lg:grid-cols-2 gap-8">
              <div>
                <h4 class="font-serif text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4">
                  Core Philosophy: Optimization of Inputs
                </h4>
                <div class="bg-secondary rounded-lg p-6">
                  <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">
                    The Productivity Approach emphasizes the efficient and
                    effective transformation of organizational inputs into
                    valuable outputs. It recognizes that productivity has
                    multiple dimensions
                    <a
                      href="https://digitallyeducate.com/contextual-perspective-of-organizational-behavior/"
                      class="citation-link"
                      >[101]</a
                    >:
                  </p>
                  <div class="space-y-3">
                    <div class="flex items-center gap-3">
                      <div class="w-3 h-3 bg-primary rounded-full"></div>
                      <span class="text-sm"
                        ><strong>Economic productivity:</strong> Ratio of
                        outputs to inputs</span
                      >
                    </div>
                    <div class="flex items-center gap-3">
                      <div class="w-3 h-3 bg-primary rounded-full"></div>
                      <span class="text-sm"
                        ><strong>Human productivity:</strong> Employee
                        satisfaction and development</span
                      >
                    </div>
                    <div class="flex items-center gap-3">
                      <div class="w-3 h-3 bg-primary rounded-full"></div>
                      <span class="text-sm"
                        ><strong>Social productivity:</strong> Organizational
                        citizenship</span
                      >
                    </div>
                  </div>
                </div>
              </div>
              <div>
                <h4 class="font-serif text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4">
                  Efficiency-Effectiveness Balance
                </h4>
                <div class="space-y-4">
                  <div class="bg-white border border-gray-200 rounded-lg p-4">
                    <h5
                      class="font-bold text-gray-900 mb-2 flex items-center gap-2"
                    >
                      <i class="fas fa-tachometer-alt text-primary"></i>
                      Efficiency
                    </h5>
                    <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 mb-2">
                      Doing things right—minimizing resource consumption
                    </p>
                    <div class="text-xs text-gray-600 bg-gray-50 p-2 rounded">
                      Risk: May produce unwanted outputs or damage quality
                    </div>
                  </div>
                  <div class="bg-white border border-gray-200 rounded-lg p-4">
                    <h5
                      class="font-bold text-gray-900 mb-2 flex items-center gap-2"
                    >
                      <i class="fas fa-bullseye text-primary"></i>
                      Effectiveness
                    </h5>
                    <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 mb-2">
                      Doing the right things—producing valuable outputs
                    </p>
                    <div class="text-xs text-gray-600 bg-gray-50 p-2 rounded">
                      Risk: May waste resources without efficiency attention
                    </div>
                  </div>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>

          <!-- Interactionalism Approach -->
          <div class="mb-12">
            <h3 class="font-serif text-2xl font-bold text-primary mb-6">
              Interactionalism Approach
            </h3>
            <div
              class="bg-gradient-to-r from-secondary to-white rounded-xl p-8 mb-8"
            >
              <div class="text-center mb-6">
                <h4 class="font-serif text-3xl font-bold text-primary mb-4">
                  B = f(P × S)
                </h4>
                <p class="text-gray-700 italic">
                  Behavior is a function of the interaction between person and
                  situation
                </p>
              </div>
              <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-6">
                <div class="text-center">
                  <div
                    class="w-16 h-16 bg-primary/10 rounded-full flex items-center justify-center mx-auto mb-3"
                  >
                    <i class="fas fa-user text-primary text-2xl"></i>
                  </div>
                  <h5 class="font-bold text-gray-900 mb-2">Person Factors</h5>
                  <ul class="text-sm text-gray-600 space-y-1">
                    <li>• Personality</li>
                    <li>• Abilities</li>
                    <li>• Values</li>
                    <li>• Motivation</li>
                  </ul>
                </div>
                <div class="text-center">
                  <div
                    class="w-16 h-16 bg-primary/10 rounded-full flex items-center justify-center mx-auto mb-3"
                  >
                    <i class="fas fa-globe text-primary text-2xl"></i>
                  </div>
                  <h5 class="font-bold text-gray-900 mb-2">
                    Situation Factors
                  </h5>
                  <ul class="text-sm text-gray-600 space-y-1">
                    <li>• Organizational culture</li>
                    <li>• Job demands</li>
                    <li>• Social norms</li>
                    <li>• Environmental constraints</li>
                  </ul>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>

            <!-- Person-Job Fit -->
            <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-8">
              <div class="bg-white border border-gray-200 rounded-xl p-6">
                <h4 class="font-serif text-lg font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4">
                  Person-Job (P-J) Fit
                </h4>
                <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">
                  Match between individual characteristics (KSAOs) and job
                  requirements.
                </p>
                <div class="space-y-3">
                  <div class="flex items-center gap-3">
                    <i class="fas fa-check text-green-600"></i>
                    <span class="text-sm">Higher job satisfaction</span>
                  </div>
                  <div class="flex items-center gap-3">
                    <i class="fas fa-check text-green-600"></i>
                    <span class="text-sm">Better performance</span>
                  </div>
                  <div class="flex items-center gap-3">
                    <i class="fas fa-check text-green-600"></i>
                    <span class="text-sm">Lower turnover</span>
                  </div>
                </div>
              </div>
              <div class="bg-white border border-gray-200 rounded-xl p-6">
                <h4 class="font-serif text-lg font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4">
                  Person-Organization (P-O) Fit
                </h4>
                <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">
                  Match between individual values and organizational culture.
                </p>
                <div class="space-y-3">
                  <div class="flex items-center gap-3">
                    <i class="fas fa-check text-green-600"></i>
                    <span class="text-sm"
                      >Higher organizational commitment</span
                    >
                  </div>
                  <div class="flex items-center gap-3">
                    <i class="fas fa-check text-green-600"></i>
                    <span class="text-sm">More citizenship behavior</span>
                  </div>
                  <div class="flex items-center gap-3">
                    <i class="fas fa-check text-green-600"></i>
                    <span class="text-sm">Cultural alignment</span>
                  </div>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>

          <!-- Contingency Approach -->
          <div class="mb-12">
            <h3 class="font-serif text-2xl font-bold text-primary mb-6">
              Contingency Approach
            </h3>
            <div class="bg-secondary rounded-xl p-8 mb-6">
              <h4 class="font-serif text-xl font-bold text-primary mb-4">
                Core Philosophy: &#34;It All Depends&#34;
              </h4>
              <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">
                The contingency approach represents a fundamental rejection of
                universal principles in favor of situation-specific analysis. It
                holds that there is no single best way to manage people or
                organize work—the most effective approach depends on specific
                circumstances
                <a
                  href="https://mrcet.com/downloads/MBA/digitalnotes/I-I/MOB%20Digital%20notes.pdf"
                  class="citation-link"
                  >[649]</a
                >.
              </p>
              <div class="bg-white rounded-lg p-4">
                <h5 class="font-bold text-gray-900 mb-2">
                  Key Contingency Variables
                </h5>
                <div class="grid grid-cols-2 md:grid-cols-4 gap-4 text-sm">
                  <div class="text-center">
                    <i class="fas fa-cogs text-primary mb-2"></i>
                    <p>Technology</p>
                  </div>
                  <div class="text-center">
                    <i class="fas fa-globe text-primary mb-2"></i>
                    <p>Environment</p>
                  </div>
                  <div class="text-center">
                    <i class="fas fa-expand text-primary mb-2"></i>
                    <p>Size</p>
                  </div>
                  <div class="text-center">
                    <i class="fas fa-heart text-primary mb-2"></i>
                    <p>Culture</p>
                  </div>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>

            <!-- "If-Then" Relationships -->
            <div class="bg-white border border-gray-200 rounded-xl p-6">
              <h4 class="font-serif text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4">
                &#34;If-Then&#34; Relationships in Practice
              </h4>
              <div class="space-y-4">
                <div class="border-l-4 border-primary pl-4">
                  <h5 class="font-bold text-gray-900 mb-2">
                    If technology is routine → Then mechanistic structure
                  </h5>
                  <p class="text-sm text-gray-700">
                    High formalization, centralization, and specialization
                  </p>
                </div>
                <div class="border-l-4 border-accent pl-4">
                  <h5 class="font-bold text-gray-900 mb-2">
                    If environment is stable → Then bureaucratic approach
                  </h5>
                  <p class="text-sm text-gray-700">
                    Standardized procedures and clear hierarchy
                  </p>
                </div>
                <div class="border-l-4 border-primary pl-4">
                  <h5 class="font-bold text-gray-900 mb-2">
                    If subordinates are unable and unwilling → Then telling
                    style
                  </h5>
                  <p class="text-sm text-gray-700">
                    Direct supervision and clear instructions
                  </p>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>

          <!-- Systems Approach -->
          <div class="mb-12">
            <h3 class="font-serif text-2xl font-bold text-primary mb-6">
              Systems Approach
            </h3>
            <div class="grid grid-cols-1 lg:grid-cols-2 gap-8">
              <div>
                <h4 class="font-serif text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4">
                  Open System Characteristics
                </h4>
                <div class="space-y-4">
                  <div
                    class="flex items-start gap-4 bg-white border border-gray-200 rounded-lg p-4"
                  >
                    <div
                      class="w-10 h-10 bg-primary/10 rounded-full flex items-center justify-center flex-shrink-0"
                    >
                      <i class="fas fa-download text-primary"></i>
                    </div>
                    <div>
                      <h5 class="font-bold text-gray-900 mb-1">Inputs</h5>
                      <p class="text-sm text-gray-700">
                        Human resources, capital, materials, information,
                        technology
                      </p>
                    </div>
                  </div>
                  <div
                    class="flex items-start gap-4 bg-white border border-gray-200 rounded-lg p-4"
                  >
                    <div
                      class="w-10 h-10 bg-primary/10 rounded-full flex items-center justify-center flex-shrink-0"
                    >
                      <i class="fas fa-sync-alt text-primary"></i>
                    </div>
                    <div>
                      <h5 class="font-bold text-gray-900 mb-1">
                        Transformation
                      </h5>
                      <p class="text-sm text-gray-700">
                        Production operations, service delivery, knowledge work
                      </p>
                    </div>
                  </div>
                  <div
                    class="flex items-start gap-4 bg-white border border-gray-200 rounded-lg p-4"
                  >
                    <div
                      class="w-10 h-10 bg-primary/10 rounded-full flex items-center justify-center flex-shrink-0"
                    >
                      <i class="fas fa-upload text-primary"></i>
                    </div>
                    <div>
                      <h5 class="font-bold text-gray-900 mb-1">Outputs</h5>
                      <p class="text-sm text-gray-700">
                        Goods, services, profits, stakeholder value
                      </p>
                    </div>
                  </div>
                  <div
                    class="flex items-start gap-4 bg-white border border-gray-200 rounded-lg p-4"
                  >
                    <div
                      class="w-10 h-10 bg-primary/10 rounded-full flex items-center justify-center flex-shrink-0"
                    >
                      <i class="fas fa-redo text-primary"></i>
                    </div>
                    <div>
                      <h5 class="font-bold text-gray-900 mb-1">Feedback</h5>
                      <p class="text-sm text-gray-700">
                        Customer surveys, financial reports, performance data
                      </p>
                    </div>
                  </div>
                </div>
              </div>
              <div>
                <h4 class="font-serif text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4">
                  Subsystems Interdependence
                </h4>
                <div class="mb-6">
                  <div class="mermaid-container">
