            </div>
            <h2 class="font-serif text-4xl font-bold text-gray-900">
              Environmental Context of Organizational Behavior
            </h2>
          </div>

          <div class="mb-8">
            <p class="text-lg text-gray-700 mb-6">
              The environmental context of OB encompasses external forces and
              trends that shape organizational conditions and create both
              challenges and opportunities for management. The TU MBS syllabus
              specifically identifies three critical environmental dimensions:
              globalization, diversity, and ethics
              <a
                href="https://www.fomecd.edu.np/syllabuses/MBS%201st%20Sem%20Syllabus%202018.pdf"
                class="citation-link"
                >[436]</a
              >
              <a
                href="http://onlinenotesnepal.com/challenges-and-opportunities"
                class="citation-link"
                >[114]</a
              >
              <a
                href="https://www.bbsnotes.com/2023/05/03/mbs-1st-semester-organizational-behaviour-model-question/"
                class="citation-link"
                >[556]</a
              >
              <a
                href="https://sist.sathyabama.ac.in/sist_coursematerial/uploads/SBAA5102.pdf"
                class="citation-link"
                >[558]</a
              >.
            </p>
          </div>

